Cut the stem of the rose down so that it is roughly the length you want it to be. Use sharp scissors or a sharp knife to cut the bottom of the stem at an angle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fb/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fb/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To determine the proper length, base the stem height on the height of the containers you will be dyeing the rose in or the height of the vase you plan to store the rose in afterward. The stem of the rose needs to be only a little taller than the length of the final vase. It should not be too much taller than the height of the dyeing containers though, or else the rose will become top-heavy and will not sit well inside the containers. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":293,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":484.3956043956044,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

In order to enjoy the most color from your paper rainbow rose, choose a square of paper with a rainbow print on the front and back. You could also choose a square sheet of paper with a white side, plain color side, or a pattern on the opposite side. Play around with different types of paper to find the look you like best. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Origami paper works especially well. The standard size for origami paper is 9 by 9 inches (23 by 23cm). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9b/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9b/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If starting with plain white paper, you can use crayons or colored pencils to color a rainbow pattern over the entire sheet of paper. For best results, try layering the colors diagonally across the square from one corner to the opposite corner. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Once you get close to the starting point of your circle, shift the cutting line in by about 1/2 inch (1.25 cm). Continue cutting around the inner perimeter of your spiral until you reach the center. The thickness of the spiral should be similar all the way around, meaning that the approximate thickness of the spiral should be about 1/2 inch (1.25 cm) evenly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut the spiral free-hand. You do not need to be precise with this technique. In fact, this rose looks best when you maintain a principle of “wabi-sabi,” a Japanese aesthetic focused on the beauty of the imperfect. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1a/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Roll the entire spiral up toward its center, rolling along the top-side of the paper. As you start, the roll should be as tight as possible. Use both hands to roll up the paper spiral. Hold the developing roll in between two fingers on one hand and use your other hand to maneuver the remaining paper around the roll to incorporate it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Initially, the final roll will look very tight and not very rose-like. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/42/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/42/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Adjust the tightness of the spiral. Slowly release the tension holding the spiral together, allowing the roll to loosen and unravel slightly while still maintaining its basic form. Let the tension drop less for a tighter roll and let it drop more for a looser rose. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add a drop of hot glue onto the top-side of the tab and firmly press it against the bottom of the rose. Make sure that each spiral is caught on the glue. Make sure to use hot glue or a glue that dries almost instantly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You also need to make sure that the edge of each spiral sticks to the glue. Otherwise, the rose may unravel once you release it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

As soon as the glue dries, set the rose down. Your paper rainbow rose should be complete. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Rainbow-Rose-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
